The paper deals with topics related to logic and algebra, specifically undecidability and rigidity of structures. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a topological framework based on closure spaces, which suggests a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The discussion of examples from symbolic dynamics suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with theorems and proofs, which suggests a connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
